{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "reto2-dummyjson-sakila-2026",
    "name": "Reto 2 - DummyJSON (Postman)",
    "description": "Reto 2 - Master Profesional en QA y Automatizacion de Pruebas.\n\nCubre los 5 ejercicios de la seccion Postman contra https://dummyjson.com.\n\n**Credenciales usadas:** emilys / emilyspass (las del enunciado `kminchelle / 0lelplR` ya no son validas en la API actual de DummyJSON).\n\n**Orden de ejecucion en Runner:** Ej 1 -> Ej 2 -> Ej 3 -> Ej 4 -> Ej 5.\n\n**Variables de entorno usadas:** `base_url`, `username`, `password`, `token`, `session_valid`, `expired_token`, `expensive_count`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Ej 1 - Login (basico)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// ===========================================================",
              "// Ejercicio 1 - BASICO: Login y validacion inicial",
              "// POST /auth/login",
              "// ===========================================================",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status code es 200', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Parseo del JSON (valida que la respuesta sea JSON valido)",
              "let jsonData;",
              "pm.test('El body se parsea correctamente como JSON', function () {",
              "    jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.be.an('object');",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Existe accessToken en la respuesta', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('accessToken');",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData.accessToken).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Username coincide con el enviado en el login', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData.username).to.eql(pm.environment.get('username'));",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Guardamos el token para los siguientes requests",
              "if (jsonData && jsonData.accessToken) {",
              "    pm.environment.set('token', jsonData.accessToken);",
              "}",
              "",
              "// ===========================================================",
              "// Soporte para Ejercicio 5 (retry):",
              "// Si entramos aca desde un 401 de /auth/me, ya refrescamos el",
              "// token arriba. Reseteamos la bandera y detenemos el runner",
              "// para evitar ciclos.",
              "// ===========================================================",
              "if (pm.environment.get('expired_token') === 'true') {",
              "    console.log('[Retry] Login de refresh exitoso. Nuevo token guardado.');",
              "    pm.environment.set('expired_token', 'false');",
              "    pm.execution.setNextRequest(null);",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{username}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "login"]
        },
        "description": "Ej 1 (basico): Login contra DummyJSON. Valida status 200, existencia de accessToken, username correcto y parseo JSON. Ademas guarda el token en la variable de entorno para los siguientes ejercicios."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Ej 2 - Auth Me (validacion de sesion)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// ===========================================================",
              "// Ejercicio 2 - INTERMEDIO: Validacion de sesion (token en uso)",
              "// GET /auth/me con Authorization: Bearer {{token}}",
              "// ===========================================================",
              "",
              "const status = pm.response.code;",
              "",
              "// Logica condicional: guardar session_valid segun el status",
              "if (status === 200) {",
              "    pm.environment.set('session_valid', 'true');",
              "",
              "    const data = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "    pm.test('Status 200', function () {",
              "        pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "    });",
              "",
              "    pm.test('Existe email en la respuesta', function () {",
              "        pm.expect(data).to.have.property('email');",
              "        pm.expect(data.email).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "    });",
              "",
              "    pm.test('Username coincide con el enviado en el login', function () {",
              "        pm.expect(data.username).to.eql(pm.environment.get('username'));",
              "    });",
              "} else {",
              "    pm.environment.set('session_valid', 'false');",
              "",
              "    pm.test('Sesion invalida registrada (session_valid = false)', function () {",
              "        pm.expect(pm.environment.get('session_valid')).to.eql('false');",
              "    });",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token}}"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/me",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "me"]
        },
        "description": "Ej 2 (intermedio): Valida la sesion usando el token guardado. Logica condicional: session_valid = true si status 200, false en caso contrario."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Ej 3 - Login (manejo de token)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// ===========================================================",
              "// Ejercicio 3 - INTERMEDIO: Manejo de token",
              "// Del login, guardar accessToken en variable 'token'.",
              "// El test debe fallar si no se guarda correctamente.",
              "// ===========================================================",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status code es 200', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "// Guardar accessToken en la variable 'token'",
              "pm.environment.set('token', jsonData.accessToken);",
              "",
              "pm.test(\"accessToken fue guardado en la variable 'token'\", function () {",
              "    const saved = pm.environment.get('token');",
              "    pm.expect(saved, 'variable token').to.not.be.null;",
              "    pm.expect(saved, 'variable token').to.not.be.undefined;",
              "    pm.expect(saved).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('El token guardado coincide con el accessToken de la respuesta', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(pm.environment.get('token')).to.eql(jsonData.accessToken);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{username}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "login"]
        },
        "description": "Ej 3 (intermedio): Centrado en el manejo del token. Guarda accessToken en la variable `token` y valida explicitamente que se haya persistido (no null, no undefined, no vacio)."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Ej 4 - Products (validacion de lista con logica)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// ===========================================================",
              "// Ejercicio 4 - DIFICIL: Validacion de lista con logica",
              "// GET /products",
              "// ===========================================================",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status 200', function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "const products = body.products || [];",
              "",
              "pm.test('Se recibio un array de productos no vacio', function () {",
              "    pm.expect(products).to.be.an('array').that.is.not.empty;",
              "});",
              "",
              "// --- Validaciones por producto (iteracion interna) ---",
              "pm.test('Todos los productos tienen price > 0', function () {",
              "    products.forEach(function (p) {",
              "        pm.expect(p.price, 'price de ' + p.title).to.be.a('number').and.to.be.greaterThan(0);",
              "    });",
              "});",
              "",
              "pm.test('Todos los productos tienen stock >= 0', function () {",
              "    products.forEach(function (p) {",
              "        pm.expect(p.stock, 'stock de ' + p.title).to.be.a('number').and.to.be.at.least(0);",
              "    });",
              "});",
              "",
              "// --- Logica condicional: price > 100 -> debe existir discountPercentage ---",
              "pm.test('Productos con price > 100 tienen discountPercentage', function () {",
              "    const caros = products.filter(function (p) { return p.price > 100; });",
              "    caros.forEach(function (p) {",
              "        pm.expect(p, 'producto ' + p.title).to.have.property('discountPercentage');",
              "        pm.expect(p.discountPercentage, 'discountPercentage de ' + p.title).to.not.be.null;",
              "        pm.expect(p.discountPercentage).to.not.be.undefined;",
              "    });",
              "});",
              "",
              "// --- Contar productos con price > 50 y guardar ---",
              "const expensiveCount = products.filter(function (p) { return p.price > 50; }).length;",
              "pm.environment.set('expensive_count', expensiveCount);",
              "",
              "pm.test('expensive_count guardado correctamente (productos con price > 50): ' + expensiveCount, function () {",
              "    pm.expect(expensiveCount).to.be.a('number').and.to.be.at.least(0);",
              "    pm.expect(Number(pm.environment.get('expensive_count'))).to.eql(expensiveCount);",
              "});",
              "",
              "console.log('Productos con price > 50:', expensiveCount);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/products?limit=100",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["products"],
          "query": [
            {
              "key": "limit",
              "value": "100",
              "description": "Traemos 100 productos para cubrir todo el catalogo de DummyJSON (son aprox 194 en total; 100 es el maximo por pagina para demostrar logica sin paginar)."
            }
          ]
        },
        "description": "Ej 4 (dificil): Recorre todos los productos y valida price > 0 y stock >= 0. Si price > 100 debe existir discountPercentage. Cuenta productos con price > 50 y los guarda en `expensive_count`."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Ej 5 - Auth Me (flujo automatico con retry)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// ===========================================================",
              "// Ejercicio 5 - DIFICIL: Flujo automatico (retry login)",
              "// - Si /auth/me responde 401 -> expired_token = true + redirigir",
              "//   al login.",
              "// - Si login es exitoso -> guardar nuevo token (lo hace Ej 1).",
              "// - Si no expira -> continuar flujo normal.",
              "// ===========================================================",
              "",
              "const status = pm.response.code;",
              "",
              "pm.test('Status esperado (200 o 401)', function () {",
              "    pm.expect([200, 401]).to.include(status);",
              "});",
              "",
              "if (status === 401) {",
              "    console.warn('[Retry] Token invalido/expirado. Redirigiendo a Login...');",
              "    pm.environment.set('expired_token', 'true');",
              "    pm.environment.set('session_valid', 'false');",
              "",
              "    pm.test('Se marco expired_token = true', function () {",
              "        pm.expect(pm.environment.get('expired_token')).to.eql('true');",
              "    });",
              "",
              "    // Redirigir automaticamente al request de Login (Ej 1)",
              "    pm.execution.setNextRequest('Ej 1 - Login (basico)');",
              "} else if (status === 200) {",
              "    pm.environment.set('expired_token', 'false');",
              "    pm.environment.set('session_valid', 'true');",
              "",
              "    const data = pm.response.json();",
              "",
              "    pm.test('Sesion vigente: existe email', function () {",
              "        pm.expect(data).to.have.property('email');",
              "    });",
              "",
              "    pm.test('session_valid = true (flujo normal continua)', function () {",
              "        pm.expect(pm.environment.get('session_valid')).to.eql('true');",
              "    });",
              "    // Sin setNextRequest: sigue el orden normal de la coleccion.",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token}}"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/me",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "me"]
        },
        "description": "Ej 5 (dificil): Flujo automatico. Si el token esta expirado (/auth/me responde 401), marca `expired_token = true` y redirige al Login (Ej 1) para refrescarlo. El Login detecta que viene de un retry y detiene el runner tras refrescar, evitando ciclos. Si el status es 200, continua el flujo normal.\n\n**Para probar el retry manualmente:**\n1. Correr la coleccion completa una vez (todo verde).\n2. En el environment, editar `token` y poner un valor invalido (ej: `invalid`).\n3. Volver a correr SOLO el Ej 5 -> recibira 401 -> se redirigira al Ej 1 -> refrescara el token -> se detendra.\n4. Volver a correr el Ej 5 -> ahora devolvera 200."
      },
      "response": []
    }
  ]
}
